race.comment: BOLD ROSIE (6) raced wide and did a good job to be beaten just 2.2 lengths on debut over 1000m at Gundagai last time out. Kept fresh since that outing six weeks ago. Only needs to hold that sort of form to be opening her account here. THE BULLET (4) struggled over 1300m at Dubbo last start after a decent first-up effort here at this trip. Gets a few key gear changes for this. Peaked third-up last prep so expect a much better performance this afternoon. ELDERBERRY WINE (7) tired when put under pressure over 1000m at Orange nine days ago. Battled on well for a minor placing here at today's journey two back - in the mix with a repeat of that effort. BINDAREE LASS (5) improved last time out at just her second appearance and from a nice draw can play a role in the finish.
